# VoltNueronGrid DB — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Rust workspace for a distributed HTAP database engine. Crates: `crates/voltnuerongrid-*`. Main service: `services/voltnuerongridd/src/main.rs` (9400+ lines). Driver: `drivers/voltnuerongrid-driver-rust/`.

## Build Commands
```bash
cargo check -p voltnuerongridd     # fast check
cargo build                         # full build
cargo test -p voltnuerongrid-sql   # SQL tests
cargo test -p voltnuerongridd       # service tests (45+)
```

## Crate Naming
- Folder: `voltnuerongrid-{name}` (hyphens)
- Import: `use voltnuerongrid_{name}::Trait` (underscores)
- Three stub crates (`voltnuerongrid-core`, `voltnuerongrid-failover`, `voltnuerongrid-meta`) — do not add logic.

## RBAC — NEVER BYPASS
Every protected endpoint must check in order:
1. `VNG_ADMIN_API_KEY` env + `x-vng-admin-key` header → `401` if missing, `403` if invalid
2. `x-vng-operator-id` + role binding → for operator paths
3. `x-vng-tenant-id` + `x-vng-user-id` → for tenant paths
Never return `200` on unauthenticated requests. Never add a `skip_auth` flag.

## Test Naming
- `ws{N}_{feature}` — workstream tests
- `h{NN}_{feature}` — hardening tests
- Tests use `#[tokio::test]`, `state_with_key()` from the test helpers module
- `state_with_key()` MUST be updated before adding new `AppState` fields

## Gate Scripts
- `tests/kpi/scripts/run-{wsN}-gate.ps1` — gate orchestrators
- `tests/kpi/results/{wsN}/` — artifacts
- Derive gate status from artifact JSON `.status`, NOT `$LASTEXITCODE`
- Use `Invoke-RestMethod` for HTTP in PowerShell — NOT `[System.Net.Http.HttpClient]`

## Security Rules
- Never log API key header values
- KMS key IDs: always `env::var("VNG_KMS_*")` — never hardcoded
- Plugin manifests must be signed; reject unsigned with `403`
- No `unwrap()` in handler paths, no `panic!` in handlers

## Known Blockers (2026-04-04)
- WS3 HTAP routing: score 40/100, routing policies incomplete, `ws3_` tests need live server
- WS1 live smokes: PowerShell `GetResponseStream` error — use `Invoke-RestMethod`
